Description:
Elegant shopfront in high-growth retail precinct
In the heart of the burgeoning Johnston/Smith Street showroom/gallery precinct, this historic shop premises has been renovated in light-flooded contemporary style. With vacant possession, here is an ideal showroom/gallery or design studio, comprising an expansive high-ceilinged principal space, large well-equipped kitchen flowing to a sunny landscaped courtyard, vast loft, fully-tiled bathroom, laundry and powder room. Zoned Commercial 2, this brilliant multi-optioned property on 135 sqm approx features polished timber floors and air conditioning.
Insights: 142 Johnston Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2016.

Description:
Ready for University!
Be Early For This One
A very spacious one bedroom ground floor apartment for Student accommodation or investment.
Generous proportion plus a user friendly design layout size is appox 50 square metre and is now available for vacant possession.
Central bathroom, generous open plan living/ dining with kitchenette.
A choice landmark solid brick secure appealing building CAMBRIDGE COURT in a mews like setting.
Featuring a roof top alfresco recreation area with stunning views.
So well located on the East Melbourne border near the Fitzroy Gardens with a tram and bus at the doorstep.
A supermarket plus shops are nearby in Smith Street plus only minutes from Australian Catholic University or just a stroll to the city or RMIT.
Suitable for Rental Investors or Student only occupiers.

Description:
Stunning terrace transformation
LEETER - Victorian elegance combined with the best in modern style, this solid-brick showpiece delivers an outstanding city-fringe lifestyle opportunity in a colourful Collingwood neighbourhood. Beyond its captivating rendered facade, the home's divine interior boasts 2 double bedrooms (both with robes) and sleek central bathroom, light-filled living area and superb new stone-top kitchen with soft-close drawers, stainless steel appliances and mirrored splashbacks. Add to this ducted heating/refrigerated cooling, new carpets and timber floors, LED lighting and more, plus a sunny north-facing courtyard with decking, integrated lighting and ROW access. Walking distance to Victoria Park Station, local buses, it's also close to vibrant shopping precincts, trendy cafes and renowned restaurants.
Insights: 178 Keele Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2016 and 29 other 2 bedroom house in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
STYLISH & SERENE CITY-EDGE SENSATION
Filled with northerly light, this first-floor Islington apartment makes an ideal city pad or quality addition to any investment portfolio with its generous design, quality features and secure surrounds. Set at the rear completely detached from the bustle of Hoddle Street, the apartment's pristine interior comprises one double bedroom (with built-in robes) and stylish central bathroom, spacious open living/dining area leading out to a fabulous full-width north-facing terrace ideal for entertaining. Add to this a well-appointed kitchen with dishwasher and stainless steel cooking appliances, split-system heating and cooling, European laundry, video intercom, plus lift to secure entry foyer and lower-level car space (easy access via Islington Street). On the fringe of East Melbourne and Richmond, it's walking distance to Victoria Parade trams, Victoria Street and Smith Street restaurants, North Richmond Station and the wide open spaces of Fitzroy Gardens. Brilliant!
Insights: 101/11 Hoddle Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2016 and 49 other 1 bedroom unit in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
City oasis with space, style and views
In a secure boutique block, this exceptional top-floor apartment is sure to make a lasting impression with its expansive design, long list of features and enviable convenience on the fringe of East Melbourne. Designer interior comprises 2 bedrooms (both with robes) and deluxe 2-way bathroom, stone-top kitchen with Fisher & Paykel appliances, vast open-plan living/dining area out to full-width entertainers' terrace with city views. Heating and cooling, hardwood floors, excellent storage spaces, lift access to foyer, 2 secure parking spaces and storage cage all add to the appeal of this exceptional apartment in a prime location walking distance to Victoria Parade trams, as well as Gertrude Street / Smith Street cafes and restaurants, local shops, supermarkets and Fitzroy Gardens. Perfect!

Great position, grand potential!

Description:
An Undeniably rare slice of the Inner Circle
Located on one of Collingwood's most picturesque streets, this single fronted terrace is immediately comfortable as is and offers scope for renovation and extension (STCA.)
This property offers two generous bedrooms, open plan living and dining, a large functional kitchen and a huge central bathroom.

Description:
EXCELLENT 2 BEDROOM APARTMENT, MOVE IN OR INVEST
Part of a near-new boutique building, this property features a south-facing entertainer's balcony, secure OSP, lift access, separate study nook, split system air-conditioning, panel heating, BIRs, quality timber floors, and loads of natural light.
Offering large living area and a further separate meals area which is unheard of in the area. The smartly designed kitchen is well appointed and boasts plenty of cupboard space, the latest SS appliances, a dishwasher and stone bench top. The two bedrooms are generously sized, both with built-in robe and a modern bathroom with a dual vanity and laundry recess.
Walk or ride your bike into the city, or take advantage of the extensive public transport network at your doorstep. An inspection is a must.

Description:
Victorian Splendour
This charming double storey residence, is positioned to take full advantage of Collingwood’s amazing attractions.
Boasting an impressive 2 Street Frontage, the home is a perfect mix of period character and contemporary style.
Featuring an inviting formal living with mantled gas/log fire, stylish kitchen with very cool pressed metal splashback, pantry, double dishwasher, family/meals, 2 double bedrooms and modern bathroom.
Combining an eclectic mix of ornate ceilings, retaining many period features, polished floors, sunroom overlooking tranquil North Facing entertainers courtyard, with plumbed gas grill and prized remote parking, from Langridge Street, for 2 cars.
With the added benefit of video entry, ceiling fans in the bedrooms, gas Rinnai heating, open fire place and sizable block, make this an ideal lifestyle abode.
Located close to the CBD, Fitzroy Gardens and popular Smith and Gertrude Street’s restaurants, cafes, bars and nightlife.
Insights: 18 Derby Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2016 and 29 other 2 bedroom house in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Vast factory conversion, outstanding potential
The former Gregory Steel Products factory, set on a huge block (465 sq.m approx) moments from Smith Street's cafe scene, is Collingwood's premier investment opportunity. Zoned Commercial 1, this grand red brick property with remnant industrial detail has brilliant scope for further development (STCA). Including 4-car garaging, a multi-room apartment/office suite with private entry and huge storeroom, this astounding building incorporates an impressively spacious residence with high ceilings, flanked by wide courtyards accessed from all principal rooms. It comprises 4 double bedrooms, expansive living and dining zones, well-equipped kitchen, 2 superbly fitted bathrooms plus large laundry, and features polished timber floors, ample storage, heating and cooling.
